column53: total_population is the total population of the community
column54: U.S. Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics Survey for 2020

column53: pct_under_5 is the percentage of the population under age 5; this value was calculated by summing the population count of multiple sex by age categories and expressing that sum as a percentage of the total population
column54: U.S. Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics Survey for 2020

column53: pct_under_18 is the percentage of the population under age 18; this value was calculated by summing the population count of multiple sex by age categories and expressing that sum as a percentage of the total population
column54: U.S. Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics Survey for 2020

column53: pct_65_plus is the percentage of the population age 65 and older; this value was calculated by summing the population count of multiple sex by age categories and expressing that sum as a percentage of the total population
column54: U.S. Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics Survey for 2020

column53: pct_hispanic_latino is the percentage of the population that is Hispanic or Latino; this value was calculated by taking the population count of Hispanics or Latinos and expressing that count as a percentage of the total population
column54: U.S. Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics Survey for 2020

column53: pct_white is the percentage of the population that is White; this value was calculated by taking the population count of Whites and expressing that count as a percentage of the total population
column54: U.S. Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics Survey for 2020

column53: pct_african_american is the percentage of the population that is African American; this value was calculated by taking the population count of African Americans and expressing that count as a percentage of the total population
column54: U.S. Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics Survey for 2020

column53: pct_amer_indian_ak_native is the percentage of the population that is American Indian or Alaska Native; this value was calculated by taking the population count of American Indians or Alaska Natives and expressing that count as a percentage of the total population
column54: U.S. Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics Survey for 2020

column53: pct_asian is the percentage of the population that is Asian; this value was calculated by taking the population count of Asians and expressing that count as a percentage of the total population
column54: U.S. Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics Survey for 2020

column53: pct_hawaiian_pacislander is the percentage of the population that is Native Hawaiian and Pacific Islander; this value was calculated by taking the population count of Native Hawaiians and Pacific Islanders and expressing that count as a percentage of the total population
column54: U.S. Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics Survey for 2020

column53: pct_other is the percentage of the population that is other race; this value was calculated by taking the population count of other races and expressing that count as a percentage of the total population
column54: U.S. Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics Survey for 2020

column53: pct_multi is the percentage of the population that is two or more races; this value was calculated by taking the population count of two or more races and expressing that count as a percentage of the total population
column54: U.S. Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics Survey for 2020

column53: pct_asthma is the percentage of adults aged >=18 years who report being diagnosed with and currently having asthma; this value is a crude prevalence rate
column54: CDC PLACES dataset for 2024

column53: pct_asthma_low is the lower bound of the 90% confidence interval for percentage of adults aged >=18 years who report being diagnosed with and currently having asthma
column54: CDC PLACES dataset for 2024

column53: pct_asthma_high is the upper bound of the 90% confidence interval for percentage of adults aged >=18 years who report being diagnosed with and currently having asthma
column54: CDC PLACES dataset for 2024

column53: pct_copd is the percentage of adults aged >=18 years who report being diagnosed with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD), emphysema, or chronic bronchitis
column54: CDC PLACES dataset for 2024

column53: pct_copd_low is the lower bound of the 90% confidence interval for percentage of adults aged >=18 years who report being diagnosed with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD), emphysema, or chronic bronchitis
column54: CDC PLACES dataset for 2024

column53: pct_copd_high is the upper bound of the 90% confidence interval for percentage of adults aged >=18 years who report being diagnosed with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD), emphysema, or chronic bronchitis
column54: CDC PLACES dataset for 2024

column53: pct_hd is the percentage of adults aged >=18 years who report being diagnosed with coronary heart disease; this value is a crude prevalence rate
column54: CDC PLACES dataset for 2024

column53: pct_hd_low is the lower bound of the 90% confidence interval for percentage of adults aged >=18 years who report being diagnosed with coronary heart disease
column54: CDC PLACES dataset for 2024

column53: pct_hd_high is the upper bound of the 90% confidence interval for percentage of adults aged >=18 years who report being diagnosed with coronary heart disease
column54: CDC PLACES dataset for 2024

column53: pct_stroke is the percentage of adults aged >=18 years who report having ever been told by a doctor, nurse, or other health professional that they have had a stroke; this value is a crude prevalence rate
column54: CDC PLACES dataset for 2024

column53: pct_stroke_low is the lower bound of the 90% confidence interval for percentage of adults aged >=18 years who report having ever been told by a doctor, nurse, or other health professional that they have had a stroke
column54: CDC PLACES dataset for 2024

column53: pct_stroke_high is the upper bound of the 90% confidence interval for percentage of adults aged >=18 years who report having ever been told by a doctor, nurse, or other health professional that they have had a stroke
column54: CDC PLACES dataset for 2024

column53: pct_diabetes is the percentage of adults aged >=18 years who report being diagnosed with diabetes (excluding diabetes during pregnancy/gestational diabetes); this value is a crude prevalence rate
column54: CDC PLACES dataset for 2024

column53: pct_diabetes_low is the lower bound of the 90% confidence interval for percentage of adults aged >=18 years who report being diagnosed with diabetes (excluding diabetes during pregnancy/gestational diabetes)
column54: CDC PLACES dataset for 2024

column53: pct_diabetes_high is the upper bound of the 90% confidence interval for percentage of adults aged >=18 years who report being diagnosed with diabetes (excluding diabetes during pregnancy/gestational diabetes)
column54: CDC PLACES dataset for 2024

column53: pct_mh is the percentage of adults aged >=18 years who report having 'frequent mental distress' (mental health including stress, depression, and problems with emotions, was not good for 14 or more days during the past 30 days); this value is a crude prevalence rate
column54: CDC PLACES dataset for 2024

column53: pct_mh_low is the lower bound of the 90% confidence interval for percentage of adults aged >=18 years who report having 'frequent mental distress' (mental health including stress, depression, and problems with emotions, was not good for 14 or more days during the past 30 days)
column54: CDC PLACES dataset for 2024

column53: pct_mh_high is the upper bound of the 90% confidence interval for percentage of adults aged >=18 years who report having 'frequent mental distress' (mental health including stress, depression, and problems with emotions, was not good for 14 or more days during the past 30 days)
column54: CDC PLACES dataset for 2024

column53: pct_minority is the percentage of the population of racial or ethnic minority status (including individuals who identified as any of the following: Hispanic or Latino (any race); Black and African American, non-Hispanic; American Indian and Alaska Native, non-Hispanic; Asian, non-Hispanic; Native Hawaiian and Other Pacific Islander, non-Hispanic; Two or More Races, non-Hispanic; Other Races, non-Hispanic)
column54: CDC PLACES Social Determinants of Health dataset for 2024 (originally derived from ACS estimates 2017-2021)

column53: pct_minority_low is the lower bound of the 90% confidence interval for percentage of the population of racial or ethnic minority status (including individuals who identified as any of the following: Hispanic or Latino (any race); Black and African American, non-Hispanic; American Indian and Alaska Native, non-Hispanic; Asian, non-Hispanic; Native Hawaiian and Other Pacific Islander, non-Hispanic; Two or More Races, non-Hispanic; Other Races, non-Hispanic)
column54: CDC PLACES Social Determinants of Health dataset for 2024 (originally derived from ACS estimates 2017-2021)

column53: pct_minority_high is the upper bound of the 90% confidence interval for percentage of the population of racial or ethnic minority status (including individuals who identified as any of the following: Hispanic or Latino (any race); Black and African American, non-Hispanic; American Indian and Alaska Native, non-Hispanic; Asian, non-Hispanic; Native Hawaiian and Other Pacific Islander, non-Hispanic; Two or More Races, non-Hispanic; Other Races, non-Hispanic)
column54: CDC PLACES Social Determinants of Health dataset for 2024 (originally derived from ACS estimates 2017-2021)

column53: pct_w_disability is the percentage of the population with a reported disability (presence of six types of disability related to serious difficulty including: hearing, vision, concentrating, remembering or making decisions (i.e. cognition), walking or climbing stairs (i.e. mobility), dressing or bathing (i.e., self-care), and doing errands alone (i.e., independent living))
column54: U.S. Census American Community Survey 5-year estimates for years 2019-2023

column53: pct_w_disability_low is the lower bound of the 90% confidence interval for percentage of the population with a reported disability (presence of six types of disability related to serious difficulty including: hearing, vision, concentrating, remembering or making decisions (i.e. cognition), walking or climbing stairs (i.e. mobility), dressing or bathing (i.e., self-care), and doing errands alone (i.e., independent living))
column54: U.S. Census American Community Survey 5-year estimates for years 2019-2023
